{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]How I'd love to hear the organ 
In the chapel in the [Em]moonlight
[A7]While we're strolling down the [D7]aisle 
[G7]Where roses [C]entwine
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[G7]How I'd love to hear you [C]whisper 
In the chapel in the [Em]moonlight
[A7]That the love light in your [D7]eyes 
[G7]Forever will [C]shine
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
Till the roses turn to [C7]ashes 
Till the [F]organ turns to [C]rust
If you never come I'll still [Am]be there 
Till the [D7]moonlight turns to [G7]dust
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
How I'd love to hear the [C]choir 
In the chapel in the [Em]moonlight
[A7]As they sing oh promise [D7]me 
[G7]Forever be [C]mine
{end_of_verse}



